ity and memory, offering a new model for analyzing the interactions between national and international images of the Holocaust.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zItaly. 0aNationalism and collective memoryzItaly. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478263040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804782630423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804782630.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles